Package: dat
Type: Package
Title: Definable Algebra Theory: Symbolic Differentiation with
        Language-Level Awareness
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Che", "Cheng", email = "lufee2005@gmail.com",
                  role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Symbolic source-transformation differentiation for vector
    calculus expressions with awareness of a four-tier first-order
    language hierarchy (L0 pure vector space, L1 inner product, L2 named
    operators, L3 analytic scalar functions). Provides a closure-preserving
    gradient operator, a user-extensible generator catalog, and a
    three-layer verification module (syntactic, numeric, cross-strategy).
    Reference implementation accompanying the Definable Algebra Theory
    framework.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
SystemRequirements: macOS (Accelerate framework) for the optional vDSP
        fast-path backend; additionally a Metal SDK and a Metal-capable
        GPU for the optional Metal compute backend (used only above
        dat.metal_threshold). Both are optional; the package builds and
        runs base-R paths without them.
Imports: stats, Rcpp
LinkingTo: Rcpp
Suggests: testthat (>= 3.0.0), Deriv, covr, devtools, bench
